1
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:07,000
（此为片前广告，正片在3:02开始）

2
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Det-sen Monasnary, Tibet
德赞寺 西藏

3
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:26,500
15年前 
（这里指1980年，因本片故事设定为1995年）

4
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:32,500
（西藏德赞寺是博士及其同伴杰米、维多利亚首次遭遇大智慧和雪怪的地方，见《神秘博士》老版本第五季第二集《可恶的雪人》 The Abominable Snowmen）

5
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:42,358
DISTORTED VOICE: Victoria...
维多利亚...

6
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:53,033
LAMA: What do you seek?
你在找什么？

7
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,475
It's me.
是我

8
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:59,517
Victoria Waterfield.
维多利亚•沃特菲尔德

9
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:02,594
Victoria...
维多利亚...

10
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:06,876
The Great Wheel turns.
命运之轮转动

11
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:10,919
You have been here once before.
你以前曾经到过这里

12
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:14,196
A long, long time ago.
很久很久以前

13
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:17,834
The monastery was in great danger.
那时候寺庙陷入了巨大的危机

14
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:21,919
You travelled a long, dark journey.
你走过了一段漫长而黑暗的旅程

15
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:28,997
How can one still so young
怎么可能如此年轻的一个人

16
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:31,475
know the depths of our darkness?
却知道我们黑暗的深处呢？

17
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,113
What has happened here?
这里发生了什么？

18
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:36,029
Turn back now.
现在回去吧

19
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:38,470
- Victoria...
-(GASPS)

20
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:41,750
My father died far away
我父亲死在一个很远的地方

21
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:45,996
- on another world.
- There are many other worlds,
- 在另外一个世界  - 有很多其它的世界

22
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,793
other planes.
其它的平面

23
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:50,434
But I can hear his voice in my thoughts.
但我能在意识里听到他的声音

24
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:53,470
He's called me all this way.
他一直都在呼唤着我

25
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:58,390
Demons and hungry ghosts
steal many shapes.
恶魔和饥饿的鬼魂偷了许多形体

26
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:01,794
Turn away, Victoria.
掉头吧，Victoria

27
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:05,999
Why do you delay? Release me!
你为什么拖延？释放我吧！

28
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:10,910
I know he's here. Please tell me where to find him.
我知道他在这里。请告诉我哪里可以找到他

29
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:15,238
A second time I ask, what do you seek?
我问第二遍，你在找什么？

30
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:17,636
(EXCLAIMS) What have you done to him?
你把他怎么了？

31
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:20,274
I'm alone in the darkness.
我独自在黑暗中

32
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:24,712
Do not disturb it. It is not your father.
别惊扰它，它不是你父亲

33
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:27,753
- Victoria?  - Let me through!
- 维多利亚？  - 让我过去！

34
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:29,029
LAMA: I cannot!
我不能

35
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:33,910
What are you hiding here? Who is it then?
你在这里藏了什么？这又是谁？

36
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:36,276
A third time I ask,
我问第三遍

37
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:38,960
what do you seek?
你在找什么？

38
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:42,832
I want the truth!
我在找真相！

39
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:49,033
You were expected.
一直在等你

40
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:54,956
My task is ended. I cannot prevent
your journey into the dark.
我的任务结束了，我不再阻止你踏入黑暗

41
00:05:56,440 --> 00:06:00,115
The truth may light your way.
真相可能可以照亮你的路

42
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:04,755
Take it.
拿着

43
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:16,151
I've been alone,
我一直一个人

44
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,191
like you, Victoria.
跟你一样，维多利亚

45
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,871
But together..
但是一起...

46
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,474
Is it you?
是你吗？

47
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,874
1 don't know.
我不知道

48
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:26,511
They said you were dead.
他们说你已经死了

49
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:28,870
But in the dreams...
但是在梦里...

50
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:32,630
- Victoria...  - Father?
- 维多利亚...  - 父亲吗？

51
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,472
(MOANING)

52
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:45,556
(FOOTSTEPS)

53
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,199
You!
是你！

54
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:51,794
Find me the Locus!
给我找到人偶！

55
00:06:52,000 --> 00:07:02,800
（Victoria 诞生于19世纪，她父亲因制造时间机器而引来Daleks，然后她和她父亲还有博士一行被 Daleks 带到 Daleks 的母星 Skaro。当 Dalek 朝博士开枪时，她父亲替他挡了一枪，因此牺牲。相关故事参见老版第四季第九集 《Dalek的邪恶》。她父亲其实跟大智慧没有什么交集，只是她自己一直因父亲的死而不能释怀。）

56
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:10,000
<b>Downtime</b>


57
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:29,278
(HOUSE MUSIC PLAYING THROUGH HEADPHONES)

58
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:36,277
No, Gordy, I told you to play down there while I'm talking.
不，高迪，我跟你说过，我在讲电话的时候你要在下面玩

59
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:37,674
Now, off you go.
现在，下来吧

60
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,838
Hello? Hello, Beth?
你好？你好，贝丝

61
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:41,919
Look, they're still there.
看，他们还在那儿

62
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:45,271
Those two, you know, New World weirdos, Chillys or whatever they're called.
这两个是什么新世界的怪人，他们称呼为鸡仔什么的

63
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:49,278
Yes, of course, I've called the police
and the council.
是的，当然，我已经报告给警察和理事会了fixme

64
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:50,993
They all think I'm crazy.
但他们觉得是我不可理喻

65
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:53,680
The Chillys just vanish when anyone comes, but they're soon back.
一有人来这些鸡仔就消失了，但很快又回来了

66
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:56,074
I mean, why pick me?
我是说，为什么挑上我？

67
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:59,758
1 don't know what to do, Beth.
I have no one else to talk to.
我不知道该怎么办，贝丝。我找不到其它人聊这个事

68
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:02,838
BETH: Look, I'll tell you what. Why
don't you try asking your dad for help?
听着，我告诉你怎么办，你为什么不找你爸爸求助？

69
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:06,311
What? Sorry, this line's terrible.
什么？抱歉，线路太不好了

70
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,311
My dad? God, no, I couldn't do that.
我爸爸？天呐，不，我不能那么干

71
00:08:09,440 --> 00:08:12,080
It's been at least six years since I spoke to him.
都至少有六年我没有跟他说过话了

72
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:14,954
Oh, and the computer keeps crashing, so I can't work.
噢，电脑一直宕机，我没法工作

73
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:18,357
And that damn noise all the time,
it's like being under siege.
一直都有那个该死的噪音，感觉像是被攻击了

74
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:20,630
Oh, it's disturbing, Gordy.
He can't stay here.
噢，这很烦人，Gordy，他不能待在这里

75
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:23,878
Would you? Would you really, Beth?
你会吗？你真的会吗，贝丝？

76
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,511
Yes. All right.
是，好吧

77
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:28,551
But soon. He can't stay here.
但快点，他不能待在这里

78
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,637
Yes, thanks, Beth. Okay, bye.
是，谢谢，贝丝。好，再见

79
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:36,000
（此角色 Kate Lethbridge-Stewart 是UNIT负责人准将 Gordon Lethbridge-Stewart 的女儿。后来她也成了UNIT的负责人，在《博士之日》中再次亮相，不过不再是这个演员）

80
00:08:36,560 --> 00:08:37,595
Gordy?
高迪？

81
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,598
{(GORDY IMITATING GUN FIRING)

82
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:42,711
No, Gordy. Not guns. Come on, darling.
不，高迪，别玩枪战了。快来，亲爱的

83
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:45,480
Now, come on up. Put that down.
Come on to the boat.
现在，上这里来。把那个放下，快到船里来

84
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,671
I've told you before about this.
Now quickly, now.
我以前跟你说过这个。快过来，马上

85
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:50,474
Here we go. Up you go. Great.
来吧，起来啰，很好

86
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:53,274
Now, you go and play inside
till Beth comes, all right?
现在，你到里面去玩，知道贝丝过来，好吗？

87
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,595
Off you go.
走你

88
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:57,836
KATE: Bloody Chillys!
要命的鸡仔！

89
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,435
Leave us alone!
走开！

90
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,799
Leave us alone.
走开

91
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,030
(WIND WHOOSHING)

92
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,954
(LOW GROWLING)

93
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:43,000
（Piccadilly Circus 皮卡迪利广场是伦敦一个路口的名称，《神秘博士》里有很多故事发生在这个地方）

94
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:08,590
MAN: (ON RADIO) The sound of the
future on 98.4 New World FM.
未来之声尽在FM98.4新世界电台

95
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:13,319
ANTHONY: (ON RADIO) And it's a Mega Morning
to all you slickers out there.
对你们所有的懒汉来说, 这是一个超级的早晨

96
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:15,292
You're jacked into N Treble U,
the ones who share,
你也许是刚刚切换到 NTU ，一个热爱分享的电台

97
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:19,792
bringing you our daily show
on National FM radio.
为你带来国家调频电台上的每日秀

98
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:22,912
I'm Anthony, and this is where
the jazzy bright day starts,
我是安东尼，轻松明亮的一天就从这里开始

99
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:25,714
a New World coming soon,
the way it always will be.
一个新世界迈步走来, 一如既往

100
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:29,509
0135-666-416.

101
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:31,912
We want to share that with you all.
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)
我们期望与你们所有人分享

102
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:35,237
Meantime, it can be a mean time out there, so let's...
与此同时，它又fixme

103
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,000
<b>(New World University)</b>
（新世界大学）

104
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:43,711
(COMPUTER READING)

105
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:03,031
(COMPUTER READING)

106
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:09,394
(HOUSE MUSIC PLAYING
THROUGH HEADPHONES)

107
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:12,080
(KEYBOARD CLACKING)

108
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:16,593
Hi, welcome to New World.
How can I help you?
嗨，欢迎来到新世界，有什么可以帮你的？

109
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:19,155
Sarah-Jane Smith, Metropolitan
magazine.
莎拉•简•史密斯，大都市杂志社

110
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:21,715
I have an appointment to see your vice chancellor.
我约好去见你的副校长

111
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:27,991
- I am expected. 
- At 11 o'clock. Would you like to take a seat?
- 他在等我  - 是11点，你可以过去坐一会儿吗？

112
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:30,440
Have the best one yet.
还有一个最佳的座位

113
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:37,199
- Miss Smith.  - Yes.
- 史密斯小姐  - 我是

114
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:39,359
Welcome to New World.
欢迎来到新世界

115
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,718
I'm so sorry if we've kept you waiting.
很抱歉让你久等了

116
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:45,029
Christopher Rice, Marketing Facilitator.
克里斯托弗·赖斯, 营销主持人。

117
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:46,195
Good morning.
早上好

118
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:48,789
- You brought the profiles with you, I hope. 
- Yes.
- 你把档案带过来了吧，我期望  - 是的

119
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:51,070
Good. Then let's go on up.
好，那我们上去再说吧

120
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,157
Miss Waterfield, the university's vice chancellor
沃特菲尔德小姐，这所大学的副校长

121
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:54,759
would like to thank you personally.
她想亲自感谢你

122
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:05,271
I think the sum agreed was 12k,
assuming all the profiles are complete.
我想总数是一万二，如果所有的档案都完整的话

123
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:06,720
Er, not quite.
呃，不太完整

124
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,873
Er, Miss Smith, when we were advised of your reputation,
哦，史密斯小姐，当有人向我们推荐你的时候

125
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,949
both Miss Waterfield and I were impressed.
沃特菲尔德小姐和我都很折服

126
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:17,994
We thought, "What's a few red-tape
barriers to a journalist of this calibre?"
我们想：“对于这样一个路子宽广的记者来说, 那些繁文缛节的障碍算什么？”

127
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:21,556
But you didn't tell me some of this data
was government classified.
但你们没告诉我这里某些数据是政府机密

128
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,557
(COMPUTER READING) Authorisation failure.
授权失败

129
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:29,833
You have 10 seconds to enter Stage Three security key.
你有10秒钟时间来输入第三阶段安全密钥

130
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:34,912
Waterfield.
沃特菲尔德

131
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:38,078
(COMPUTER READING)
You are attached to Priority Zone Z.
你已经连接到优先区域Z区

132
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:41,000
（他眼镜中呈现的图像很像是大智慧的三角锥/金字塔）

133
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:42,389
Yes!
成了！

134
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:46,513
Look, I still don't know
what New World wants these people for.
看，我还是不知道新世界要这些人的资料做什么

135
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:48,717
Afraid of unearthing a scandal?
害怕发现一桩丑闻？

136
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:51,251
Half of them vanish off any records.
他们中有一半从所有记录里消失了

137
00:12:51,560 --> 00:12:54,200
And what is this "London Event”
that connects them?
与他们都相关的这个“伦敦事件”又是什么？

138
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,276
What do you know?
你知道些什么？

139
00:12:57,240 --> 00:13:00,631
I've found records implying
that 25 years ago
我发现有记录显示，在25年前

140
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:03,832
Central London was evacuated
in an industrial accident.
伦敦市中心因一起工业事故，出现过大规模疏散的事

141
00:13:03,952 --> 00:13:05,560
（应该是指1970年前后的大智慧和雪怪入侵事件，见第五季第二季《恐惧之网》，不过该事件的具体时间不详）

142
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:09,116
They say it lasted three months.
There are no extant reports.
他们说这事持续了三个月，但目前没有见到有报告保存下来

143
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:11,959
No one even remembers.
Well, how can that happen?
也没有人记得。你说，这怎么可能呢？

144
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:16,194
The London Event was a wasted opportunity.
伦敦事件是一次被浪费掉的契机

145
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:20,880
The world missed out on an interface
with a higher plane of existence.
这个世界错过了一个与更高层面存在打交道的接口

146
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:23,149
It's no big deal.
这没什么要紧

147
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:25,993
There will be other chances.
还会有其它机会的

148
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:28,836
It was totally misunderstood.
这被完全误解了

149
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:32,157
We all stumbled about
in the unknowing darkness.
我们都还困在莫名的黑暗中

150
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:34,840
New World seeks to
light the first candle.
新世界致力于点亮第一根蜡烛

151
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,435
Oh, come on.
噢，得了

152
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:38,870
New World's more than just
a New Age Sunday School.
新世界不仅仅是一所新时代的主日学校

153
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,673
You've got fingers in more pies
than Robert Maxwell.
你们的手指比罗伯特·马克斯维尔还多fixme

154
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:46,159
I'm afraid we've wasted your time, Miss Smith.
恐怕我们耽误你的时间了，史密斯小姐

155
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:48,669
You already knew.
你已经知道了

156
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:50,669
New World has the solution.
新世界找到解决方案了

157
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,279
That's our motto.
这是我们的座右铭

158
00:13:54,080 --> 00:13:55,718
Our programme.
我们的课程

159
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:59,314
If you've got such high-flying sources,
why employ me?
如果里面有如此高的消息来源，为什么还雇我？

160
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:02,396
There is one name
missing from your list.
你的清单里少了一个名字

161
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:05,878
Not to my knowledge.
据我所知没有

162
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,435
But much to ours.
但对我们很重要

163
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:12,075
Lethbridge-Stewart.
利斯布里奇-斯图尔特。

164
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,831
What do they want old Stewpot for?
他们找这个老斯图做什么？

165
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:22,518
United Nations Intelligence Task-force
is a paramilitary espionage squad.
UNIT（联合国情报部门行动组）是一个准军事间谍小组

166
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:25,510
It's the old MI5 story.
这是老旧的军情五处类的故事

167
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:30,032
Everyone knows it's there, but no
one knows what its real agenda is.
每个人都知道它的存在，但没有人清楚它的真正目标是什么

168
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:33,232
Even those who work for it.
即使是那些为他工作的人

169
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:38,876
Alistair Gordon Lethbridge-Stewart figures
largely in its setting up in the '70s.
在它70年代的成立过程中，
Listair Gordon Lethbridge-Stewart 扮演了很重要的角色

170
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:42,436
By then, he's a brigadier
with a remarkable active service record.
那时，他是一个准将, 有着出色的服役记录

171
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:45,118
And then he vanishes.
然后他就消失了

172
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:49,078
You must have known him
during your time with UNIT.
你肯定认识他，那段时间你也在UNIT

173
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:52,713
Sorry to disappoint you,
but I'm just a journalist.
让你们失望了，我只是一个记者

174
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:56,713
With no official records
of Lethbridge-Stewart,
由于没有关于 Lethbrige-Stewart 的官方记录

175
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:59,994
one could easily imagine he was dead.
其他人就会很轻易地认为他已经死了

176
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,999
UNIT looks after its own.
UNIT 会保护他们自己人

177
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:04,477
What's this brigadier
supposed to have done?
你们觉得这个准将都做了什么？

178
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:06,952
He has committed a great crime.
他犯了一项巨大的罪行

179
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:10,200
But there are other ways of seeking him.
但还是有其它方法找到他

180
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:12,789
(SPHERE BEEPING)

181
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:14,676
(BANG)

182
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:20,519
(PULSATING)

183
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:31,829
(SPHERE BEEPING AND PULSATING)

184
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:33,473
Someone in the secure system.
有人进入了安全系统

185
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,398
- What's happening?
- Daniel Hinton.
- 怎么回事？ - 是丹尼尔·辛顿

186
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:39,832
- That devious little...
- I don't want him hurt, Christopher.
- 那个狡猾的小...  - 我不想他受伤，克里斯托弗

187
00:15:39,960 --> 00:15:41,075
Of course.
当然

188
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:47,839
(HOUSE MUSIC PLAYING
THROUGH HEADPHONES)

189
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:50,236
MAN: (ON RADIO) And that's the
Acoustic Hoods here at Top o'the Clock.

190
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:52,033
You're jacked into N Treble U
你收听的是 NTU 电台

191
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:54,436
from New World,
the people with the solution,
由有解决方案的人 - 新世界为你带来

192
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:56,471
and we ain't talking watered down here.
我们的节目不兑水

193
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:59,114
If you can't get your
head round life, no hassle.
如果你不能从生活中抬起头来，没有问题

194
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:02,278
There's over 300 different courses
here at New World.
新世界有300多种不同的课程

195
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,471
So there's got to be a right one for you,
hasn't there?
所以总有一款适合你，是吧？

196
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:07,194
Give us a call. 0135-66...
给我们来电话，0135-66...

197
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:20,350
There he is!
他在那儿！

198
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:34,796
(SPHERE BEEPING AND PULSATING)

199
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:37,472
What is New World University?
新世界大学是什么？

200
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:40,629
You don't have lectures.
You don't even have tutors.
你们没有讲座，你们连老师都没有

201
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:44,672
All the tuition is
conducted by the mainframe,
所有的授课都是由靠电脑主机来进行

202
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:46,871
a personalised syllabus for every student.
为每个学生提供个性化的教学大纲

203
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:49,431
Since when did computers get
personal?
电脑什么时候开始有个性了？

204
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:52,036
(BEEPING AND PULSATING)

205
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:03,193
Come on, what are the Chillys really for?
说说，鸡仔真正是干什么的

206
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:05,118
A sort of a fascist hippy cult?
一种法西斯嬉皮士邪教？

207
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:10,351
The wicked world is full of lost children,
the aimless, the lonely.
这个邪恶的世界里到处都是失落的孩子, 漫无目的, 孤独无助

208
00:17:11,080 --> 00:17:14,675
We follow the Det-sen disciplines
which we share with our Chancellor.
我们遵循德赞信条，这点我们与校长是一致的

209
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:17,750
We really do care.
我们真的在意

210
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:21,153
Well, where is he then? Why can't I see him?
那，他在哪儿？我怎么见不到他？

211
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:23,032
The Chancellor sees no one.
校长不见任何人

212
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:26,759
He has taken the Path of Truth.
他已经走上了真理之路

213
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:29,353
Victoria Waterfield.
维多利亚•沃特菲尔德

214
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:32,670
That's you on the list, isn't it?
At the London Event?
在名单上的是你，对不？伦敦事件的时候

215
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:35,433
Oh, you must have been really young.
噢，你那时一定很年轻

216
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:38,996
Considering I was born
over 140 years ago...
考虑到我是140多年前出生的...

217
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:42,554
Peanuts, I used to know someone who...
花生，我以前认识一个能够-fixme

218
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:43,715
Oh, never mind.
噢，算了

219
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:47,637
Oh, sorry, I mean, no,
you don't look a day over...
哦，抱歉，我是说，你看起来一天也没有...

220
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:50,752
I don't feel a day over. (LAUGHING)

221
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:56,356
(COMPUTER READING ON LOOP)
Find the Locus.
找到人偶

222
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:03,959
(WHIMPERS)

223
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:08,069
We all have pain to face, Sarah,
我们都有痛苦要面对，莎拉

224
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:11,600
but the revelation will be soon.
但启示很快就会出现

225
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:16,598
(COMPUTER READING ON LOOP)

226
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:21,350
(SPHERE BEEPING AND PULSATING)

227
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:24,080
(HOUSE MUSIC PLAYING
THROUGH HEADPHONES)

228
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,270
Come on, Daniel.
来吧，丹尼尔

229
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:32,278
Nothing to be afraid of.
没什么可害怕的

230
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:34,679
We're here to help you.
我们是来帮你的

231
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:37,194
You've been chosen.
你被选中了

232
00:18:45,480 --> 00:18:46,470
It's a sham!
这是假象！

233
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:48,079
The whole thing!
这整件事！

234
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:49,679
It'll get you all!
它会抓到你们所有人！

235
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:52,476
It already has you, Daniel.
它已经抓到你了，丹尼尔

236
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,235
Go on, then.
继续啊

237
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:58,357
There's no escape, not even that way.
你没法逃掉了，就是那边也不行

238
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:03,953
-(DANIEL SCREAMING)
-(WHISPERING) Daniel!
丹尼尔！

239
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:13,515
-(WIND HOWLING)
-(CROWD CHATTERING)

240
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:16,155
MAN: Ball!
球！

241
00:19:49,520 --> 00:19:50,715
Sir? Please, sir?
长官？打扰了，长官

242
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:53,995
Hinton? What are you doing here?
辛顿？你在这里做什么？

243
00:19:54,120 --> 00:19:56,509
Hinton, D.A., sir. School House 91.
辛顿, 地方检察官, 长官。学校房子91 fixme

244
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:04,153
It must be a good three years
since you got yourself expelled.
你被开除后这三年过得肯定很不错

245
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:07,591
Yes, sir, but I need to talk to you now.
Sir, It's important.
是的, 长官, 但我现在需要和你谈谈。 长官，很重要的事

246
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:12,792
Frankly, Hinton, I don't know
how you could throw it all away.
坦白说, 辛顿, 我不知道你怎么能把这一切都扔掉

247
00:20:13,520 --> 00:20:15,750
You excel at maths and
computer work...
你擅长数学和计算机工作..

248
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:18,633
The headmaster says
I'm "a disruptive influence”.
校长说我“破坏性的影响”

249
00:20:18,760 --> 00:20:19,989
It wasn't deliberate, sir.
这不是故意的，长官

250
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:24,634
No more than losing your CCF kit
or skiving off games.

251
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:26,920
(SIGHS) This occult nonsense.
这太荒诞了

252
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:29,275
(SIGHS) This occult nonsense.
这太荒诞了

253
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:32,153
Dabbling with black magic
is a dangerous business.
玩弄黑魔法太危险了

254
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:35,318
It was a séance, sir.
Not magic, or drugs.
那是个邪教，长官。没有魔法，没有磕药

255
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:38,034
- No?  - I've done it loads of times.
- 不是？ - 我已经做过好多次了

256
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:39,554
I suppose it's a gift.
我想这是种天份

257
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:42,316
You have no idea
what you're dealing with.
你完全不知道你在对付什么

258
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:44,556
No, sir. Not natural, is it?
不知道，长官。超自然的东西，对不？

259
00:20:47,520 --> 00:20:49,272
Do you have a family, sir?
你有家庭吗，长官？

260
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:56,316
You realise we're under surveillance.
你意识到我们被监视了吧

261
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:07,272
Tsk. Wretched boy.
唉, 可怜的男孩

262
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:25,511
(DISTORTED) Where is the Locus?
人偶在哪儿？

263
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:28,109
Who are you?
你是谁？

264
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:33,118
(MONSTER GROWLING)

265
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:42,115
(STATIC)

266
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:44,390
ANSWERING MACHINE: This is Alistair
Lethbridge-Stewart at Brendon.
这里是布伦登的Alistair
Lethbridge-Stewart家

267
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:46,591
Leave your name, number
and message after the tone,
在嘀的一声后，留下你的名字、电话和留言

268
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:48,393
and I'll call you back
as soon as possible.
我会尽快给你打回去的

269
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:49,715
(ANSWERING MACHINE CLICKS)

270
00:21:49,840 --> 00:21:53,595
WOMAN: Oh, hello, er, Brigadier?
This is the headmaster's secretary.
噢，你好，准将。这里是校长秘书处

271
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:55,836
We were concerned
that you missed the meeting
你没来参加，我们很关切

272
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:57,792
about your retirement party this morning.
今早是你的退休欢送会

273
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:02,032
We've also had several rather
strange phone enquiries about you.
我们还接到几个奇怪的电话，都是在问你的问题

274
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:04,879
Could you get in touch ASAP?
Thank you.
你能尽快与我们联系吗，谢谢

275
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,320
(ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS)

276
00:22:06,440 --> 00:22:08,078
I thought I was in Cromer.
我以为我在克罗默fixme

277
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:16,032
-(STATIC STOPS)
-(CROWD CHATTERING)

278
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:20,155
Tuesday?
星期二了？

279
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:48,271
(ANSWERING MACHINE REWINDING)

280
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:11,829
(ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS)

281
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:16,032
KATE: Look, erm, it's me, Dad.
是这样，嗯，是我，爸爸

282
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:18,276
- I'm sorry, I know it's been a long time.
- Kate!
- 我很抱歉，我知道太长时间了  - 凯特！

283
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:21,074
This'll be a shock and all that...
but can I see you?
这很突然而且又...但我能见你吗？

284
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:22,915
Soon please, Dad.
尽快好吗，爸爸

285
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:27,959
Sorry. It's, erm, 0585-226-904.
抱歉，我的号码是0585-226-904

286
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:31,310
Erm, thanks. (BEEPS)
嗯，谢谢

287
00:23:31,440 --> 00:23:35,035
(ANSWERING MACHINE)
Saturday, 3:44 p.m.
星期六，下午 3:44

288
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:38,954
Stupid machine.
Can't have been asleep that long.
愚蠢的机器。我不可能睡了那么久

289
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:42,590
(CROWD CHATTERING)

290
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:54,674
(BEEPS)

291
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:58,637
MALE VOICE:
Greyhound is asked to call Trap Six.
有要求让灰狗呼叫陷阱六号
(灰狗 Greyhound 是 UNIT 中一个小组的代号，Brigadier 自己是灰狗一号）

292
00:23:58,760 --> 00:24:02,435
I repeat, Greyhound is to call Trap Six.
重复一遍，灰狗将呼叫陷阱六号

293
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:08,755
- ANSWERING MACHINE: Monday, 10:05 a.m.
- Monday? What ever happened to Sunday?
- 星期一，上午 10:05  - 星期一？星期天哪儿去了？

294
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:13,437
(SCOFFS) Nonsense.
No one sleeps for three days.
胡扯，没人能一觉睡三天

295
00:24:18,520 --> 00:24:20,511
(PHONE RINGING)

296
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:25,959
-(STATIC)
- Brendon School.
这里是布伦登学校

297
00:24:27,480 --> 00:24:28,629
Who is this?
是哪位？

298
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:30,114
SARAH: Hello? Brigadier?
你好，准将吗？

299
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:32,790
- This is Sarah-Jane Smith.
- Miss Smith?
- 我是莎拉-简·史密斯  - 史密斯小姐？

300
00:24:33,560 --> 00:24:36,279
Yes. Look, just please listen.
You could be in danger.
是的。请听我说，你可能有危险

301
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:38,232
I've just come from
New World University...
我刚从新世界大学出来...

302
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:40,479
-(STATIC) -Hello? Brigadier!
能听到吗？准将！

303
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:45,590
-(PULSATING)
-(PLAYING ON LOOP) Brendon school.

304
00:24:49,680 --> 00:24:50,875
We have him.
我们找到他了

305
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:58,118
Hi, kids. Been in
any good deprograms lately?
嗨, 孩子们。最近有什么好的节目吗？

306
00:24:58,240 --> 00:24:59,674
Want any autographs?
想要谁的签名不？

307
00:25:00,520 --> 00:25:01,840
If you can read, that is.

308
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:10,235
(DOOR OPENS)

309
00:25:16,560 --> 00:25:19,837
- Looking for something, Anthony?
- A producer with a sense of humour.
- 在找什么吗，安东尼？  - 找一个有幽默感的制作人

310
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:21,997
-(CHUCKLES)
- I want a word with the high priestess.
我想和高级女祭司说句话

311
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:23,958
I'm afraid the vice chancellor's busy.
恐怕副校长这会儿正忙

312
00:25:24,080 --> 00:25:27,914
The conviction I give your propagandist
crap should win me a BAFTA.

313
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:30,759
I can't get into my office
for ruddy computer hardware.

314
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:33,474
Well, it's all part of the new
automated transmitter programme.

315
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:36,319
- Then get the transmitter
to read the scripts. (CHUCKLES)

316
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:38,158
There's no people left here.
这里都没有人了

317
00:25:38,280 --> 00:25:41,398
It's just computers
and brain-dead Chillys.
只有电脑和无脑的鸡仔

318
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:43,633
I'll tell Miss Waterfield.
我会同沃特菲尔德小姐讲的

319
00:25:44,560 --> 00:25:46,631
Tell her I want action now.
告诉她我要看见行动

320
00:25:46,760 --> 00:25:50,390
Not when orders come down from our
Glorious Sponsor, wherever he hangs out.

321
00:25:54,800 --> 00:26:00,034
DISTORTED VOICE: This blind,
empty outer-darkness is unendurable!
这个盲目的, 空虚的外面黑暗是无法忍受的!

322
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:03,275
Release me now!
释放我吧！

323
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:06,199
I gave you my word. Soon.
我向你承诺过了，快了

324
00:26:11,560 --> 00:26:14,951
(SIGHS) I don't belong in this world.
我不属于这个世界

325
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:19,876
My family and friends, all lost in time.
我的家庭和朋友，都迷失在时间里了

326
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:24,512
We are both outcast, Victoria.
我们都是被放逐的人，维多利亚

327
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:27,916
That is why we work together.
所以我们要携手

328
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:31,676
I built you this place,
我给你建了这个地方

329
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:36,998
with the money my dear
father invested 130 years ago
用了我父亲130年前投资所产生的收益

330
00:26:37,680 --> 00:26:42,038
In return, you promised us
the Light of Truth.
作为回报，你许诺给我们真相之光

331
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:45,437
(SCOFFS) There is no Light.
没有光

332
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:49,953
I trust you, Victoria.
我相信你，维多利亚

333
00:26:50,920 --> 00:26:54,800
One Locus still binds my power.
还有一个人偶困住我的能力

334
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:57,877
The others were dealt with.
其它的都已经处理掉了

335
00:26:58,400 --> 00:27:02,792
The last must... Will be ready for my
return.
最后一个必须...为我的回归做好准备

336
00:27:06,480 --> 00:27:09,916
I think I'm going to scream.
我觉得我要尖叫了

337
00:27:12,320 --> 00:27:14,596
Trap Six, this is Greyhound.
What is your message?

338
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:16,154
{STATIC)
{INDISTINCT)

339
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:20,035
Please repeat, Trap Six.
It's an appalling line.
请再说一遍，陷阱六号。这信息很震惊

340
00:27:21,760 --> 00:27:22,830
In London?
在伦敦吗？

341
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:25,991
Roger, Trap Six, message understood.
收到，陷阱六号，明白了

342
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:44,276
(ENERGY PULSATING)

343
00:27:57,080 --> 00:28:00,072
(CROWD APPLAUDING)

344
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:18,756
The brigadier's on the move...
准将出动了...

345
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:20,598
Daniel Hinton?
丹尼尔·辛顿呢？

346
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:21,994
He fell from the roof.
他从屋顶上掉下去了

347
00:28:23,080 --> 00:28:24,593
What are you saying?
你在说什么？

348
00:28:24,720 --> 00:28:27,109
Just jumped.
There's no sign of him below.
他跳下去了，但下面没有见到他的踪迹

349
00:28:28,200 --> 00:28:29,474
But no one could...
但没人能...

350
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:32,239
Why didn't you tell me?
你怎么不早告诉我？

351
00:28:33,080 --> 00:28:34,957
Poor Daniel. We must find him!
可怜的丹尼尔。我们必须找到他！

352
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:37,280
Let me explain again.
让我再解释一下

353
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:41,590
He's vanished.
His programme's ring-fenced.

354
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:43,313
He cannot deprogram himself.

355
00:28:43,880 --> 00:28:46,713
Horrible modern terms. You deal with it.
可怕的现代术语。你来处理吧

356
00:28:47,840 --> 00:28:50,309
My task is to prepare the way.

357
00:28:51,320 --> 00:28:52,993
Not found the Locus yet then?
还没有找到人偶吗？

358
00:28:54,240 --> 00:28:58,757
Christopher, the chancellor is coming home.
克里斯托弗, 校长要回来了

359
00:29:00,560 --> 00:29:02,631
VICTORIA: It seems the time is now.
看来现在到时候了

360
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:05,800
I must find the last Locus
我必须找到最后一个人偶

361
00:29:06,480 --> 00:29:10,553
before Daniel's misguided hopes
wreck everything we've worked for.
免得被误导的丹尼尔会破坏我们为之奋斗的一切

362
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:26,671
Bleeding loaded.

363
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:30,240
Let it go, will ya? I was only looking!
放手吧，行吗？我只是看看

364
00:29:53,160 --> 00:29:54,355
(WHISPERS) God.
老天

365
00:29:55,880 --> 00:29:56,836
(SIGHS)

366
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:00,559
(HORN HONKING)

367
00:30:09,800 --> 00:30:10,915
The Locus...
那个人偶...

368
00:30:26,360 --> 00:30:28,715
I'll break your fingers, you little...
我要掰断你的手指，你个小...

369
00:30:28,840 --> 00:30:30,717
(FOOTSTEPS)

370
00:30:31,720 --> 00:30:33,836
No, no... (MUFFLED GRUNTING)
不，不...

371
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:36,637
(HORNS BLARING)

372
00:30:40,360 --> 00:30:41,680
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

373
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:46,076
- I'm trying to get through there,
but it's worse. - Yeah. Excuse me...
- 我本打算从这边过去，但更不好走  - 是，抱歉...

374
00:30:53,040 --> 00:30:54,235
It's coming closer.
它越来越近了

375
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:57,429
Perhaps you have
something it needs, sir.
也许你手里有它要的东西

376
00:30:57,960 --> 00:31:00,998
After all this time?
I rather doubt that, Hinton.
这么些年以后？我很是怀疑，辛顿

377
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:04,117
But you remember
what it was, don't you?
但你记得是什么东西，对吗？

378
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:09,597
BRIGADIER: I'm not as blinkered
as people think.
我并不像人们想象的那么睁眼瞎

379
00:31:10,360 --> 00:31:12,636
It's a sort of mind parasite.
它像是一种意识寄生虫

380
00:31:12,760 --> 00:31:16,037
- The first alien force I ever came up against.
- Sir?
- 是我第一次遭遇的外星力量  - 长官？

381
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:19,278
In those days it called itself
The Great Intelligence.
那个时候它自称为“大智慧”

382
00:31:19,400 --> 00:31:20,435
And?
还有呢？

383
00:31:20,560 --> 00:31:24,918
No physical shape of its own,
so it enslaved humans as pawns.
它没有它自己的物理形体, 所以它就奴役人类作为它的爪牙

384
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:30,636
And it deployed a squad of strategic
robots camouflaged like Yeti.
它还部署了一队战斗机器人, 伪装成雪怪的样子

385
00:31:31,320 --> 00:31:32,674
Was this in Tibet, sir?
那是在西藏吗, 长官？

386
00:31:33,520 --> 00:31:36,399
No. London, about 25 years ago.
不, 伦敦, 大概25年前

387
00:31:37,280 --> 00:31:39,749
It invaded the city like a virus,
它像病毒一样入侵了这个城市

388
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:44,036
using the Underground network
as its nervous system.
把地铁网络用作了它的神经系统

389
00:31:45,240 --> 00:31:48,790
Grisly business.
I thought we were rid of the blighter.
可怕的事情。我以为我们已经摆脱这个可恶的家伙了

390
00:31:48,920 --> 00:31:50,433
It's still here, sir,
它还在这里, 长官

391
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:53,234
out on the bardo, the astral plane,
躲在中阴之中, 五行之外
<i>（中阴：藏传佛教术语, 指灵魂处于死后与重生之间时的状态）</i>

392
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:55,715
trapped outside our physical existence.
被困于我们物理存在之外

393
00:31:55,840 --> 00:31:57,353
BRIGADIER: Is it indeed?
确实吗？

394
00:31:57,480 --> 00:31:58,709
And what does it want?
那它想要什么？

395
00:31:58,840 --> 00:32:00,319
I don't know, sir.
我不知道, 长官

396
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:01,794
It's you it's hunting.
它在追寻的是你

397
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:07,835
(GASPS)

398
00:32:12,320 --> 00:32:14,038
What's this got to do with you, Hinton?
但这怎么又跟你扯上了关系, Hinton？

399
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:15,639
Just don't trust anyone, sir.
别相信任何人, 长官

400
00:32:15,760 --> 00:32:17,910
- What?  - No one at all.
- 什么？ - 无论是谁

401
00:32:18,680 --> 00:32:22,036
Look, I'll thank you, Hinton,
not to treat me like a complete idiot.
嗯, 我得感谢你, Hinton, 没把我当做一个完全的傻子

402
00:32:23,240 --> 00:32:25,277
(HORNS BLARING)

403
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:32,709
(YETI GROWLING)

404
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:40,233
Damn traffic. Brings out the worst
in you, doesn't it?
可恶的交通, 把每个人最坏的一面都带出来了, 是吧？

405
00:32:41,240 --> 00:32:42,753
(HORN HONKING)

406
00:32:43,520 --> 00:32:44,749
DISTORTED VOICE: Daniel Hinton.
丹尼尔·辛顿

407
00:32:45,560 --> 00:32:47,039
You are summoned.
你被召唤了

408
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:50,551
(WHIMPERING) Sir, get off me!
先生, 离我远点！

409
00:32:51,760 --> 00:32:53,114
Daniel Hinton!
丹尼尔·辛顿

410
00:32:53,240 --> 00:32:55,277
My summons binds you!
我召唤你！

411
00:32:58,560 --> 00:33:00,551
MAN: (ON RADIO) Traffic update
on New World FM.
新世界FM播报交通状况

412
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:02,870
ANTHONY: (ON RADIO) I think you'd
better stay home today.
我觉得你们最好今天待在家里

413
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:04,991
On top of a ton of traffic probs,
除了一大堆交通堵塞

414
00:33:05,120 --> 00:33:08,238
they've just announced that all the
railways and major airports are suspended.
他们刚刚还宣布了铁路和主要机场都关闭

415
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:11,432
<i>So, you'd better get walking 'cause
they're shutting down the tube, too.</i>
所以你最好步行, 因为他们又要关闭隧道了

416
00:33:11,560 --> 00:33:13,676
Crazy. Everything has computer flu.
疯了, 所有东西都患上了电脑病毒似的
<i>(招牌文字: 电脑混沌在蔓延)</i>

417
00:33:13,800 --> 00:33:17,229
So, whatever you do, don't log into your PCs.
所以, 不管你干什么, 今天都不要登入电脑

418
00:33:17,320 --> 00:33:19,829
They're in a mean mood today.
(ALARM CHIRPS)
它们今天心情很不爽

419
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:25,557
Can I tell you about the New World, sir?
我能跟你介绍一下新世界吗, 先生？

420
00:33:25,680 --> 00:33:26,954
I'm not interested.
我不感兴趣

421
00:33:27,080 --> 00:33:28,673
We want to tell you
about our good news, sir.
我们想跟你说说我们的好消息, 先生

422
00:33:28,800 --> 00:33:30,598
I said I'm not interested.
我说了我不感兴趣

423
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:34,310
Have a better one.
找个更好的吧(fixme)

424
00:33:34,440 --> 00:33:38,399
And that's the best of the weather,
brought to you by New World University
这是最好的天气, 新世界大学为你们带来

425
00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:40,158
where the sun always shines.
而阳光永远灿烂

426
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:41,715
Gridlock out there.
外面交通大堵塞

427
00:33:41,840 --> 00:33:43,990
Is it Friday the 13th,
and they didn't tell us?
难道今天是黑色星期五, 而他们没有告诉我们？

428
00:33:44,120 --> 00:33:45,440
Stay at home, give us a call.
待在家里, 给我们打电话

429
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:48,439
0135-666-416.

430
00:33:48,560 --> 00:33:51,200
And on line one, it's Danny.
一号线接通了, 这位是丹尼

431
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:53,118
Hi, Daniel. What's your problem?
嗨, 丹尼尔, 你什么问题？

432
00:33:53,240 --> 00:33:56,153
HINTON: Anthony, it's me. I'm still alive.
安东尼, 是我, 我还活着

433
00:33:56,280 --> 00:33:58,590
- Listen. It's coming.
- Danny, you idiot. What's happening?
- 听我说, 它要来了  - 丹尼, 你个笨蛋, 都怎么回事？

434
00:33:58,720 --> 00:34:00,074
It's already coming for me,
but it wants all of us.
它已经来找我了, 但它要我们全部

435
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:02,271
- You've got to warn...
- I knew you'd get caught! Where are you?
- 你必须得警告...  - 我就知道你会被抓住的！你在哪儿？

436
00:34:03,200 --> 00:34:05,237
Danny, you've got to get help before we...
丹尼, 你必须找人帮忙, 否则我们...

437
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:08,591
Danny! Danny!
丹尼！丹尼！

438
00:34:09,040 --> 00:34:11,429
(ENERGY PULSATING)

439
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:18,751
{STATIC)
{GROANING)

440
00:34:21,200 --> 00:34:23,635
-(SIGHS)
- What are you after?
你在追什么？

441
00:34:25,240 --> 00:34:26,639
Bloody Chillys.
要命的鸡杂

442
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:29,954
- I'm going to get the law.
- Think they'd believe you?
- 我打算去找执法部门了  - 觉得他们会相信你？

443
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:33,714
Sir, I never hurt no one.
先生, 我从没伤害过任何人

444
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:36,832
Not me, sir. Not old Harrods.
不是过, 先生, 不是老哈罗斯

445
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:39,315
(SHOUTS) Don't!
不要！

446
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:42,075
Sir,
先生

447
00:34:43,800 --> 00:34:45,791
flew right down, you did.
飞下来了, 你那时候

448
00:34:45,920 --> 00:34:49,311
Glided down out of that place. (LAUGHS)
从哪个地方滑下来了

449
00:34:50,040 --> 00:34:52,475
Don't need jets no more, sir?
不在需要滑翔机了吗, 先生？

450
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:56,389
And then he comes after us,
like an old spidery man.
然后他就开始追着我们, 像一只老蜘蛛

451
00:34:56,840 --> 00:34:58,319
He's coming after all of us.
他在追我们所有人

452
00:34:59,920 --> 00:35:03,117
Listen, that money you nicked from me
is no good to anyone. Period!
听着, 你从我身上摸走的钱对谁也没有好处。句号！

453
00:35:03,240 --> 00:35:04,674
Not unless you help me!
除非你帮助我？

454
00:35:05,920 --> 00:35:07,035
You got more?
你还有吗？

455
00:35:09,400 --> 00:35:12,119
Sir, 1 got principles.
先生, 我有原则的

456
00:35:12,760 --> 00:35:14,319
I'm very particular.
我非常挑剔

457
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:17,480
You've seen what's coming,
你看到什么东西会来

458
00:35:20,040 --> 00:35:22,077
but it's only half what I see.
但不及我说看到的一半

459
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:25,034
Come on, there's someone
we have to reach fast.
快, 我们必须得尽快找到一个人

460
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:37,434
- Good morning.
- Hi. How can I help you?
- 早上好  - 嗨, 有什么可以帮你的吗？

461
00:35:37,560 --> 00:35:38,880
Lethbridge-Stewart for Cavendish.
利斯布里奇-斯图尔特, 来找凯文迪许

462
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:40,911
Right. If you'd like to go through
to the lounge, Brigadier,
好, 如果你走过休息室, 准将

463
00:35:41,040 --> 00:35:43,953
you'll find Captain Cavendish
already waiting for you.
你就会发现凯文迪许队长已经在等你

464
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:49,073
"John Jerum, soldierman,
Is searching high and low.
"John Jerum, 兵哥哥, 上下求索"

465
00:35:50,080 --> 00:35:54,677
"The only secret he can keep
Is one he doesn't know.”
“唯一能保住的秘密, 是他自己也不知道的”

466
00:35:56,840 --> 00:35:58,672
My father used to say that.
我父亲经常念这句

467
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:01,239
He'd have hated this.
他肯定恨这个

468
00:36:03,160 --> 00:36:05,310
You haven't got a clue, have you?
你一点都不知道, 是吧

469
00:36:06,120 --> 00:36:09,238
Your precious Chancellor's
got all the real power,
你那宝贵的校长拥有所有真正的能力

470
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:11,351
the power we can all profit by.
我们都可以从这些能力里受益

471
00:36:12,640 --> 00:36:15,439
He isn't just some
father substitute for you.
他可不是你那什么父亲的小替身

472
00:36:15,560 --> 00:36:18,154
He works for the world's spiritual good,
他致力于建立一个很好的精神世界

473
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:20,832
but you'd even sell your own soul.
但你却把自己的灵魂都卖了

474
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:23,520
(CHUCKLES) That's marketing.
这是市场营销

475
00:36:24,480 --> 00:36:26,517
All "ring-fenced” no doubt.

476
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:29,752
Like your expense account.

477
00:36:31,120 --> 00:36:32,633
ANTHONY: (LOUDSPEAKERS)
Victoria Waterfield!
维多利亚•沃特菲尔德!

478
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:34,554
Can you hear me?
你能听到我吗？

479
00:36:35,200 --> 00:36:38,670
Miss Waterfield's our boss,
ladies and gentlemen,
沃特菲尔德小姐是我们的老板, 女士们先生们

480
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:41,758
- the big cheese at N Treble U!
- Make him stop! Stop him!
- 她是 NTU 的重要任务！  - 让他停下来！阻止他！

481
00:36:41,880 --> 00:36:44,076
-(CHUCKLES)
- And she's today's surprise guest
她是今天的神秘嘉宾

482
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:45,873
on “Lift the Lid.”
来到“揭开盖子”栏目

483
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:48,594
So, ring in those questions now.
好, 现在打电话进来提问吧

484
00:36:48,720 --> 00:36:51,872
It's revelation time, Vice Chancellor!
到了揭晓的时间了, 副校长！

485
00:36:52,920 --> 00:36:55,912
Forget anything I said before.
It was lies!
忘了我以前说过的话吧, 都是谎言！

486
00:36:56,440 --> 00:36:58,670
New World's just a big front.
新世界只是一个大幌子

487
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:01,758
But they pay well, don't they,
Miss Waterfield?
不过他们薪水不错, 是吧, 沃特菲尔德小姐？

488
00:37:02,600 --> 00:37:04,910
-(ENERGY PULSATING) - What about
all the people that disappear, eh?
但那些失踪的人呢, 嗯？

489
00:37:05,040 --> 00:37:06,439
Danny was right!
丹尼说对了！

490
00:37:06,560 --> 00:37:09,029
New World doesn't give a toss for you.
新世界并不在乎你

491
00:37:09,160 --> 00:37:10,230
Something's coming.
有东西来了

492
00:37:10,720 --> 00:37:12,631
Victoria Waterfield will tell you.
维多利亚•沃特菲尔德会告诉你们的

493
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:15,199
(SOBBING) She'll tell you.
她会告诉你们

494
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:19,276
And it'll finish everything.
那东西会结束这一切

495
00:37:31,800 --> 00:37:34,360
- Good to see you, Brigadier.
- Sorry I'm late, Cavendish.
- 很高兴见到你, 准将  - 抱歉我来晚了, 凯文迪许

496
00:37:34,480 --> 00:37:37,438
The transport system seems to be
fouled up by this computer business.
交通系统似乎被电脑问题搞瘫痪了

497
00:37:37,560 --> 00:37:40,234
- Mmm, quite. Would you care for a drink?
- No, thank you.
- 唔, 太差了。你介意喝一杯吗？  - 不, 谢谢你

498
00:37:40,880 --> 00:37:42,598
I thought it best to meet here.
我觉得在这里见面最好

499
00:37:42,720 --> 00:37:45,439
Security boys get a bit stressed out
over ID checks.
负责安全的小伙子们总是要紧张兮兮地查证件

500
00:37:46,080 --> 00:37:48,720
So, UNIT hasn't changed since my time, eh?
看来, 我走之后 UNIT 还没变, 嗯？

501
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:51,354
Well, I doubt there'd be much left
that you'd recognise.
哦, 我怀疑还有多少你能认识

502
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:53,949
Razor-smart weapons,
all are computers these days.
Razor-smart 的武器, 现在全是电脑了fixme

503
00:37:54,880 --> 00:37:58,157
I used to leave the technology to the
experts.
我那时都把技术问题留给专家

504
00:37:58,280 --> 00:37:59,918
Yes, of course.
是, 当然

505
00:38:01,160 --> 00:38:03,993
Do you know they called your era
"The Blunder Days"?
你知道他们把你们那个时代叫做“Blunder时代”吗？

506
00:38:04,120 --> 00:38:06,316
- The what?
- Blood and Thunder.
- 什么时代？  - 热血和雷霆

507
00:38:06,440 --> 00:38:08,556
Well, you took on
some formidable opposition.
看, 你碰上了一些强硬的对手

508
00:38:08,680 --> 00:38:11,513
Cybermen, demons, Yeti.
赛博人, 恶魔, 雪怪

509
00:38:12,560 --> 00:38:16,633
No worse than jumped up officers
with tuppenny-halfpenny commissions.

510
00:38:17,520 --> 00:38:18,874
Right.
对

511
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:21,992
Cavendish, exactly why did you call me
up to town today?
凯文迪许, 你今天到底是为了什么把我叫进城来？

512
00:38:22,120 --> 00:38:23,872
Information, sir,
资料, 长官

513
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:27,874
of a personal nature, you understand?

514
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:29,274
Meaning?
意思是...？

515
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:31,789
Someone's been hacking
into security files in Geneva.
有人黑进了日内瓦的保密文件

516
00:38:31,920 --> 00:38:33,513
My files, I take it.
我的文件, 我懂了

517
00:38:33,640 --> 00:38:36,632
Yes, so the MOD were never very
forthcoming about dealings with UNIT.
是的, 所有

518
00:38:36,760 --> 00:38:39,673
Besides, we need more personal details.
另外, 我们需要多一些个人信息

519
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:40,756
We?
我们？

520
00:38:41,480 --> 00:38:44,233
Do I take it that security is in the dark
about this, too?

521
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:48,273
Strange you never rose
above Brigadier, wasn't it?
奇怪的是你做准将之后再也没有升值过, 是吗？

522
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:50,598
Internal politics.
内部政治

523
00:38:51,880 --> 00:38:55,157
Well, I had no idea there was a market
for my memoirs.
啊, 我还不知道我的回忆录还挺有市场

524
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:58,389
I'll send you a copy
when I get round to writing them.
等我有时间写完的话, 我会送你一本

525
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:07,400
So, UNIT got all the blame
for blowing up the church.
所以, 炸掉教堂的事情就全是 UNIT 背锅了？fixme

526
00:39:07,520 --> 00:39:08,555
(CHUCKLES)

527
00:39:09,840 --> 00:39:12,354
- Are you sure you won't join me, Brigadier?
- Quite sure.
- 你确定不陪我来一杯, 准将？ - 相当确定

528
00:39:14,160 --> 00:39:16,879
You must've picked up
the odd souvenir in your time.
你那时肯定拿过一些奇怪的东西

529
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:21,196
I counted them in
and I counted them all back out.
收进来的时候我数过, 放回去的时候我哦也数过

530
00:39:21,320 --> 00:39:23,914
No particular keepsake?
没有什么特别的纪念品？

531
00:39:24,040 --> 00:39:25,713
I mean, things do get mislaid.
我是说, 弄丢什么东西

532
00:39:26,200 --> 00:39:29,397
If you lose things,
you could lose men, too.
如果你弄丢东西, 你也会弄丢人

533
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:33,676
Well, it's been good to talk to you, Cavendish.
but I have another appointment.
好了, 很高兴同你聊聊。凯文迪许。但我还有另外一个约

534
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:36,440
So soon? I was concerned, Brigadier.
这么快？我很担心, 准将？

535
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:38,676
- So was I
- CAVENDISH: So you should be.
- 我也是  - 你也该这样

536
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:41,719
Blood and Thunder, Captain.
热血与雷霆, 队长fixme

537
00:39:41,840 --> 00:39:43,194
Now back off.
现在退后

538
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:45,160
I'm leaving.
我走了

539
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:49,559
Get after him!
去追他！

540
00:39:52,160 --> 00:39:53,594
It's not too late!
还不算太迟！

541
00:39:54,360 --> 00:39:55,998
I must find it.
我必须找到它

542
00:39:56,760 --> 00:39:59,434
(PYRAMID PULSATING)

543
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:03,076
DISTORTED VOICE: Victoria, I am here.
维多利亚, 我在这里

544
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:23,311
(DISTORTED) Where is the Locus?
人偶在哪里？

545
00:40:24,680 --> 00:40:26,671
(HORNS BLARING)

546
00:40:32,160 --> 00:40:36,996
All right then.
Quote them the codes, NN and then QQ.
那好吧, 告诉他们代号, NN 和 QQ
<i>(分别指《可恶的雪人》和《恐惧之网》对应事件,
其实它们是相应电视剧集的生产代号)</i>

547
00:40:38,560 --> 00:40:41,837
It's a risk, but we must reach
someone we can trust.
这是个风险, 但我们必须找到一个我们可以信任的人

548
00:40:57,200 --> 00:40:59,271
(STATIC)

549
00:41:00,640 --> 00:41:05,237
- MAN: (ON PHONE) Q?
- No, I said codes NN and Q... QQ!
- Q?  - 不, 我说了, 代号是 NN 和 Q .. QQ！

550
00:41:05,360 --> 00:41:06,759
- It's urgent!
- I see, thank you.
- 这事很紧急！  - 明白了, 谢谢你

551
00:41:06,880 --> 00:41:08,200
I'd get more sense from a tea lady.
找个女服务员都比你明白

552
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:10,072
May I ask if you've encountered
anything resembling a Yeti?
我可以问问, 你是遇到了某种像是雪怪的东西？

553
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:12,430
- Have I encountered any what?
- A Yeti.
- 我是遇到了什么？ - 雪怪！

554
00:41:12,560 --> 00:41:14,471
What have Yeti got to do with it?
雪怪跟这有什么关系？

555
00:41:21,440 --> 00:41:23,477
- You're late.
- I was delayed.
- 你迟到了  - 我被拖住了

556
00:41:23,600 --> 00:41:26,479
The traffic and this computer business...
堵车和电脑方面的问题...

557
00:41:26,600 --> 00:41:29,160
- Are you all right?
- Oh, I can't complain.
- 你还好吗？  - 噢, 没什么可抱怨的

558
00:41:29,280 --> 00:41:30,509
How are you?
你好吗？

559
00:41:31,320 --> 00:41:32,754
Look, this is stupid.
看, 这事很愚蠢

560
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:34,314
I'll just go. I shouldn't have called you.
我还是走吧, 不应该给你打电话的

561
00:41:34,440 --> 00:41:37,558
Look, Kate, have you eaten?
We could get a meal.
嗯, 凯特, 你吃了吗？我们可以去吃个饭

562
00:41:37,680 --> 00:41:39,557
No. Ugh...
不, 呃...

563
00:41:39,680 --> 00:41:42,479
- All right, er, we'll sit here.
- 1... (SIGHS)
- 没事, 嗯, 我们就这里坐坐  - 我...

564
00:41:43,680 --> 00:41:45,318
I'm sorry, Dad.
对不起, 爸爸

565
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:50,594
You look tired.
你看起来很累

566
00:41:50,720 --> 00:41:52,199
I've had a difficult morning.
我这一早上过得很糟糕

567
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:55,990
Kate, it's been six years.
凯特, 这都六年了

568
00:41:56,120 --> 00:41:57,315
What's the matter? Is it money?
出什么事呢？是因为钱吗？

569
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:58,794
No, no. Not especially.
不, 不。并不是

570
00:41:58,920 --> 00:42:01,594
- Your mother then?
- No! I don't see her either.
- 那是你母亲？  - 不！我也没见她

571
00:42:02,640 --> 00:42:05,200
Look, I know this is crazy, but...
看, 我知道

572
00:42:05,320 --> 00:42:06,913
- I'm being harassed.
- Who by?
- 我被骚扰了  - 被谁？

573
00:42:07,600 --> 00:42:09,477
- There are these Chillys.
- Chillys?
- 就那些鸡仔  - 鸡仔?

574
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:11,193
- You know? Children...
-(EXCLAIMS) Children?
- 你知道吗, 一些孩子...  - 孩子？

575
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:14,233
I mean they're called Children
from this New World techno-cult.
我是说他们被一个新世界的科技崇拜团队称为孩子

576
00:42:14,360 --> 00:42:15,509
Two of them.
有两个人

577
00:42:15,640 --> 00:42:17,551
They just sit opposite the boat
all the time.
他们一直坐在船的对面

578
00:42:17,680 --> 00:42:19,717
- Look, I'm being stupid.
- No.
- 看, 我是个蠢人...  - 不

579
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:21,751
But they just won't go away.
但他们就是不走

580
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:24,918
And they're frightening...
And they're frightening me.
而且他们很吓人...他们让我害怕了

581
00:42:26,040 --> 00:42:27,360
Chancellor.
校长

582
00:42:33,320 --> 00:42:36,551
Welcome home, Professor Travers.
欢迎回来, Travers 教授

583
00:42:36,680 --> 00:42:39,638
(DISTORTED) I am still in the wilderness.
还还在荒野里

584
00:42:41,320 --> 00:42:45,439
Only my will to survive
keeps me from despair.
都靠我求生的欲望才使我免于绝望

585
00:42:46,320 --> 00:42:49,199
You have lit a flame of hope in all of us.
你在我们中间点起了希望的火焰

586
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:54,756
It is as I instructed.
它是按照我的指示

587
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:58,235
Symmetry. Shape.
对称. 形状

588
00:42:58,360 --> 00:43:02,149
My form at last,
最后是我的形体

589
00:43:02,280 --> 00:43:04,430
shaping out my future!
决定了我的未来！

590
00:43:07,080 --> 00:43:11,950
When will my new web
stretch out across the Earth?
什么时候我的新网才能布满整个地球？

591
00:43:12,080 --> 00:43:13,036
Web?
网？

592
00:43:14,080 --> 00:43:19,154
Only when I have found the final Locus!
只有等我找到最后的人偶！

593
00:43:20,200 --> 00:43:21,759
But what about, erm...
但那个谁, 嗯...

594
00:43:21,880 --> 00:43:23,473
What's his name? Doesn't he help?
他的名字是什么来着？他帮不上忙吗？

595
00:43:23,600 --> 00:43:25,591
I split up with Jonathan two years ago.
我同乔纳森分开了, 两年前

596
00:43:25,720 --> 00:43:27,119
I'm sorry.
对不起

597
00:43:27,240 --> 00:43:28,833
I'm getting old.
我老了

598
00:43:28,960 --> 00:43:30,473
Perhaps you should get off that boat.
也许你应该离开那艘船

599
00:43:30,600 --> 00:43:32,398
It's not the boat. It's them!
问题不是船, 是他们！

600
00:43:33,040 --> 00:43:34,792
- And me too?
- Well,
- 我也是吗？  - 怎么说呢

601
00:43:35,600 --> 00:43:38,194
army families get to live together,
so why didn't we?
军人家庭一般都住在一起, 为什么我们不是？

602
00:43:38,320 --> 00:43:40,118
Was your career that important?
你的事业就那么重要？

603
00:43:41,680 --> 00:43:44,035
I'm afraid I can't explain, Kate.
恐怕我没法解释, 凯特

604
00:43:44,160 --> 00:43:46,674
Mum used to think that
you were some sort of spy.
妈妈曾经以为, 你是某种间谍

605
00:43:46,800 --> 00:43:49,314
We used to hope it, because at least
that would be interesting.
我们曾经都盼望过, 因为那样的话就会很有意思

606
00:43:50,080 --> 00:43:51,479
But it's just soldiers, isn't it?
但你只是一个士兵, 是吗？

607
00:43:52,120 --> 00:43:54,873
Training to kill people with big guns.
被训练成用大枪去杀人

608
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:56,718
I had other responsibilities.
我扛着其它一些责任

609
00:43:56,840 --> 00:43:58,319
Well, who to?
哦, 对谁的责任？

610
00:43:58,440 --> 00:44:00,397
To everyone.
对每一个人

611
00:44:00,520 --> 00:44:01,954
What?
什么？

612
00:44:02,080 --> 00:44:03,036
That's all.
只能说这么多

613
00:44:03,160 --> 00:44:05,436
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

614
00:44:09,120 --> 00:44:10,599
Who do I trust, then?
那, 我信任谁？

615
00:44:12,120 --> 00:44:16,034
Don't trust anyone, sir.
I told you, no one at all.
别相信任何人, 长官。我告诉过你, 无论是谁

616
00:44:20,000 --> 00:44:21,832
Are you sure you don't want any money?
你确定不想要些钱吗？

617
00:44:21,960 --> 00:44:23,439
Oh, just forget it then.
噢, 忘了这事算了

618
00:44:24,560 --> 00:44:26,073
Kate. Kate, wait!
凯特, 凯特, 等等！

619
00:44:27,320 --> 00:44:29,596
(HOUSE MUSIC PLAYING THROUGH HEADPHONES)

620
00:44:32,960 --> 00:44:36,112
Hello again, Granddad. We want you.
又遇到了, 老爷爷, 我们在找你

621
00:44:36,240 --> 00:44:37,196
Argh!
啊！

622
00:44:48,520 --> 00:44:49,669
Good Lord...
好家伙...

623
00:44:50,200 --> 00:44:52,157
Is that you?
是你吗？

624
00:44:52,280 --> 00:44:55,352
Have you changed yourself again?
你又变样子了？
<i>（显然这里准将以为这又是博士的新化身）</i>

625
00:44:59,720 --> 00:45:04,957
<i>Om mani padme hum</i>
<i>(唵嘛呢叭咪吽)</i>

626
00:45:04,920 --> 00:45:06,957
I needed time!
我需要时间!

627
00:45:07,640 --> 00:45:09,313
DISTORTED VOICE: I needed freedom!
我需要自由！

628
00:45:10,040 --> 00:45:11,872
You're not Professor Travers!
你不是 Travers 教授！

629
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:13,479
-(LAUGHING)
- A pity shame!
可怜可耻！fixme

630
00:45:13,600 --> 00:45:15,398
Let me go!
放开我！

631
00:45:15,520 --> 00:45:17,670
Your task is done.
你的任务完成了

632
00:45:17,800 --> 00:45:20,235
Now, I take control!
现在, 我掌握控制权了

633
00:45:21,280 --> 00:45:22,873
Let me go!
放开我

634
00:45:23,520 --> 00:45:25,079
Who are you?
你是谁？

635
00:45:25,720 --> 00:45:27,631
Remember me, Victoria?
记得我吗, 维多利亚？

636
00:45:28,280 --> 00:45:30,351
Who's blind now?
现在谁是瞎子？

637
00:45:34,080 --> 00:45:35,832
- Hello, Dad.  - Kate.
- 嗨, 爸爸  - 凯特

638
00:45:37,040 --> 00:45:38,553
- Where am I?  - On the boat.
- 我在哪儿？  - 在船上

639
00:45:38,680 --> 00:45:39,670
We had to bring you here.
我们只能带你来这里

640
00:45:39,800 --> 00:45:42,474
Daniel Hinton, Brigadier. School House 91.
我是丹尼尔·辛顿, 准将。布伦登学校91届

641
00:45:43,200 --> 00:45:45,237
I remember. Thank you.
我记得。谢谢你

642
00:45:46,400 --> 00:45:47,959
But we met quite recently. Am I right?
但我们最近碰过面, 我说得对吗？

643
00:45:48,080 --> 00:45:50,515
On something called the astral plane?
在一个被称为意识层面的地方？

644
00:45:50,640 --> 00:45:52,119
It wasn't entirely wasted then.
看来没有全白费

645
00:45:52,240 --> 00:45:53,560
Extraordinary.
令人惊奇

646
00:45:54,840 --> 00:45:56,638
Hello? We're moving.
怎么？我们在走

647
00:46:01,360 --> 00:46:02,873
Dad, I thought it would be best if...
爸爸, 我觉得最好还是...

648
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:04,434
Sir... Glad to see you're all right, sir.
长官...很高兴看见你没事, 长官

649
00:46:04,560 --> 00:46:06,471
Harrods saved you from the Chillys.
哈罗斯从鸡仔手中救了你

650
00:46:06,600 --> 00:46:08,079
Bunch of hooligans, sir.
一群小流氓而已, 长官

651
00:46:08,200 --> 00:46:09,554
Best off well away from them.
最好离他们远一点

652
00:46:09,680 --> 00:46:12,035
Well, thank you, erm... Harrods?
好, 谢谢你, 呃...哈罗斯？

653
00:46:12,160 --> 00:46:13,150
Sir.
是

654
00:46:13,280 --> 00:46:15,556
Army, aren't you? On your uppers?
军人, 对不？在你鞋帮上fixme

655
00:46:15,680 --> 00:46:20,993
RAF, sir. Flight Sergeant Haroldson.
Squadron got disbanded, sir.
皇家空军, 长官。空军上士哈罗德森。中队编制被取消了, 长官

656
00:46:22,120 --> 00:46:23,872
Like losing your family.
就像没了家一样

657
00:46:25,960 --> 00:46:29,396
Get called Harrods
'cause I'm fussy where I kip down.
被叫做哈罗斯, 因为我对于睡觉的地方很挑剔

658
00:46:29,520 --> 00:46:31,955
- Alright, Flight Sergeant. Carry on.
- Sir.
- 好吧, 空军上士, 继续  - 是

659
00:46:34,520 --> 00:46:37,478
I must say, Kate,
the company you keep's an eye-opener.
我必须要说, 凯特, 你这些朋友很让人开眼

660
00:46:37,600 --> 00:46:38,999
Oh, I thought they were with you.
哦, 我还以为他们是你一伙儿的

661
00:46:39,120 --> 00:46:42,078
We can't stay here, Brigadier,
the Intelligence is hunting us.
我们不能待在这里, 准将。大智慧在搜寻我们

662
00:46:42,200 --> 00:46:45,830
The both of us? Are you one of these
Chilly characters too?
我们两个都是？你不也是那些鸡仔中的一员吗？

663
00:46:46,360 --> 00:46:49,318
New World's a front to bring
the Intelligence back through,
新世界只是一个外壳, 意图是要把大智慧带回来

664
00:46:49,440 --> 00:46:51,272
an evil spirit that
got bound to the Earth.
那是个恶灵, 被困到地球了

665
00:46:51,880 --> 00:46:55,874
Listen to you two. I mean, who do I
call first, police or psychiatrist?
听听你们两个。我是说, 我应该先打电话给谁, 警察还是精神病医生？

666
00:46:56,000 --> 00:46:58,879
Trust no one. Isn't that right, Hinton?
别信任何人。这没错吧, 辛顿？

667
00:46:59,000 --> 00:47:02,197
- Not even my people at the UNIT.
- The whole city's fouled up.
- 即使是我那些 UNIT 的人  - 整个城市都混乱了

668
00:47:02,320 --> 00:47:04,709
The computer Internet's virally infested.
电脑互联网已经被病毒入侵了

669
00:47:04,840 --> 00:47:06,877
And that's the Intelligence's new body?
那就是大智慧的新形体？

670
00:47:07,880 --> 00:47:09,075
It won't stop there.
它不会止步于此的

671
00:47:14,360 --> 00:47:16,158
(BEEPING)

672
00:47:16,280 --> 00:47:19,398
The Intelligence was driven out.
I was there.
大智慧被赶走了, 当时我在那里

673
00:47:19,520 --> 00:47:23,115
No. It's trapped until all its old
icons of power can be destroyed.
没有, 它只是被困住了。fixme

674
00:47:23,920 --> 00:47:27,117
One link still remains, the final Locus.
有一个链接还在, 最后那个人偶

675
00:47:27,240 --> 00:47:29,117
- Well, how do you know?
- Just do.
- 哦, 你怎么知道？  - 就是知道

676
00:47:30,320 --> 00:47:33,039
Cavendish asked me about keepsakes.
卡文迪许问过我是否保留了纪念品

677
00:47:33,160 --> 00:47:34,309
And now that I think of it,
现在我再想想

678
00:47:34,440 --> 00:47:36,078
- there was something.
- Yes?
- 好像是有某个东西  - 是吗？

679
00:47:36,200 --> 00:47:37,713
But I lost that years ago.
但多年以前弄丢了

680
00:47:37,840 --> 00:47:38,796
Like what?
什么样子的？

681
00:47:39,440 --> 00:47:42,637
A small carving of a Yeti,
like a chess piece.
一个雪怪一样的小雕像, 像一个象棋棋子

682
00:47:42,760 --> 00:47:44,034
Tibetan, I think.
西藏的东西, 我想是

683
00:47:45,040 --> 00:47:45,996
Dad...
爸爸...

684
00:47:47,960 --> 00:47:49,553
(BEEPING)

685
00:48:04,920 --> 00:48:06,035
Like this?
就像这个？

686
00:48:07,080 --> 00:48:09,469
Yes. That's it.
是的, 就是它

687
00:48:09,600 --> 00:48:11,193
I've had it since I was little.
我很小的时候拿了它

688
00:48:11,320 --> 00:48:13,994
It's infinitely dangerous.
We must get rid of it now.
这东西非常的危险, 我们必须马上甩掉它

689
00:48:14,680 --> 00:48:15,750
(CRASHING)

690
00:48:15,880 --> 00:48:17,075
Sir?
长官？

691
00:48:17,400 --> 00:48:18,720
Sir, we have company.
长官, 有客人来了

692
00:48:22,520 --> 00:48:24,670
No, get them away! Get them away!
不, 把他们弄走！把他们弄走！

693
00:48:24,800 --> 00:48:26,711
- Everyone, out, now!
- I'm sorry, Brigadier.
- 所有人, 出去, 马上！  - 抱歉, 准将

694
00:48:26,840 --> 00:48:28,194
Out of the way, Hinton.
别碍事, 辛顿

695
00:48:28,320 --> 00:48:29,799
I didn't know, I swear it.
我不知道, 我发誓

696
00:48:29,920 --> 00:48:31,319
What are you on about?
你这是干什么？

697
00:48:31,440 --> 00:48:34,159
I warned you! Don't trust anyone!
我告诉过你！不要相信任何人！

698
00:48:34,280 --> 00:48:37,238
The Intelligence used me to seek you out.
I'm the trap!
大智慧利用我来把你挖出来, 我就是诱饵！

699
00:48:37,360 --> 00:48:39,431
I'm warning you, Hinton, stand back!
我警告你, 辛顿, 后退！

700
00:48:39,560 --> 00:48:41,073
- Give me the Locus.
- KATE: No.
- 把人偶给我  - 不

701
00:48:41,480 --> 00:48:43,198
No guns. Not here!
不要开枪, 这里不行！

702
00:48:43,320 --> 00:48:45,914
- Get back!
-(BEEPING)
后退!

703
00:48:52,720 --> 00:48:54,791
(ROARING)

704
00:49:02,720 --> 00:49:03,835
(GROWLING)

705
00:49:17,440 --> 00:49:19,397
What's happening? This is my home.
发生了什么？这里是我家

706
00:49:20,120 --> 00:49:23,033
Well, they got what they want
and now they're going.
喏, 他们得到了他们想要的东西, 现在就撤了

707
00:49:23,760 --> 00:49:25,637
Back to the New World, sir.
回新世界去了, 长官

708
00:49:25,760 --> 00:49:27,353
That's where it all comes from.
他们都来自那个地方

709
00:49:27,480 --> 00:49:29,073
What sort of job do you do?
你干的是什么工作？

710
00:49:29,200 --> 00:49:31,157
- That boy...
- I have to get after them, Kate.
- 那个孩子...  - 我必须得去追他们, 凯特

711
00:49:31,280 --> 00:49:32,600
I'll explain later.
我后面再解释

712
00:49:32,720 --> 00:49:33,994
Just go, then.
走吧, 那就

713
00:49:34,120 --> 00:49:35,190
Flight Sergeant?
空军上士？

714
00:49:35,320 --> 00:49:37,675
I'll come, sir. For the lad's sake.
我也去, 长官。为了那个小伙子

715
00:49:37,800 --> 00:49:39,029
Good man.
好人

716
00:49:39,160 --> 00:49:40,798
Er, wait outside, will you?
呃, 外面等一下, 好吗？

717
00:49:40,920 --> 00:49:41,876
Sir.
是

718
00:49:45,400 --> 00:49:46,834
- Kate.
- What?
- 凯特  - 什么？

719
00:49:47,560 --> 00:49:48,755
Just tell me one thing.
就告诉我一件事情

720
00:49:49,880 --> 00:49:52,156
Why do you keep a box of toys down there?
为什么你在这里存了一箱玩具？

721
00:49:59,560 --> 00:50:01,073
He'll be five, next week.
他就要满五岁了, 下个星期

722
00:50:04,520 --> 00:50:06,431
(SOFTLY) I have a grandson!
我有一个外孙了！

723
00:50:08,040 --> 00:50:10,919
My grandson!
我的孙子！

724
00:50:11,040 --> 00:50:12,838
I never dreamt...
我从没梦想过...

725
00:50:13,920 --> 00:50:14,876
Good Lord.
好家伙

726
00:50:15,600 --> 00:50:16,556
Gordon.
他叫戈登

727
00:50:17,440 --> 00:50:19,113
Gordon James, after you.
戈登-詹姆斯, 用你的名取得

728
00:50:20,600 --> 00:50:22,398
He's safe, away from here.
他很安全, 不在这里

729
00:50:23,320 --> 00:50:24,355
Oh, I'm sorry.
哦, 对不起

730
00:50:24,480 --> 00:50:26,551
(SNIFFLES) My grandson.
我的外孙

731
00:50:27,440 --> 00:50:29,113
Kate, can I keep this?
凯特, 我能留着这个吗？

732
00:50:29,560 --> 00:50:31,198
It's getting late.
时候不早了

733
00:50:31,320 --> 00:50:33,357
We'll talk later. I'll be back.
我们晚些再谈, 我会回来的

734
00:50:43,440 --> 00:50:45,477
(GROWLING)

735
00:50:50,280 --> 00:50:51,395
(DISTORTED) At last.
终于

736
00:50:53,240 --> 00:50:55,754
I created this tiny object
我创造了这个小东西

737
00:50:57,120 --> 00:50:59,839
and it has bound me in darkness.
而它把我困在了黑暗中

738
00:51:04,400 --> 00:51:06,676
Which of you shall release me?
你们谁来释放我？

739
00:51:13,040 --> 00:51:14,394
(EXPLODING)

740
00:51:15,520 --> 00:51:17,591
Light...
光...

741
00:51:18,520 --> 00:51:19,874
(GROANING)

742
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:25,234
Symmetry of colours and shapes.
对称的颜色和形状

743
00:51:26,840 --> 00:51:30,629
No more tomb of darkness.
不再有黑暗的坟墓了

744
00:51:33,560 --> 00:51:37,997
My strength is growing again.
我的力量又开始增长了

745
00:51:39,880 --> 00:51:42,076
I grasp it.
我抓住了

746
00:51:42,200 --> 00:51:48,515
Now let my great plan take its shape.
现在让我的伟大计划成形吧

747
00:51:49,160 --> 00:51:51,151
(ENERGY PULSATING)

748
00:51:58,400 --> 00:52:01,119
(ALL CHANTING) Om mani padme hum.
唵嘛呢叭咪吽

749
00:52:13,320 --> 00:52:15,152
TRAVERS: (NORMAL VOICE)
I had a daughter once.
我曾经又一个女儿

750
00:52:15,800 --> 00:52:18,553
What... What happened to her?
怎么...她后来怎么了？

751
00:52:19,320 --> 00:52:20,594
Father?
父亲？

752
00:52:22,880 --> 00:52:26,077
No, no. Not you. Anne.
不, 不, 不是你。安娜

753
00:52:26,880 --> 00:52:27,836
(CHUCKLES)

754
00:52:28,400 --> 00:52:30,437
Yeti...Travers...I...
雪怪...Travers...我...

755
00:52:32,840 --> 00:52:35,229
I brought it...
我带回了它...

756
00:52:36,440 --> 00:52:38,113
...back from Tibet.
...从西藏带来

757
00:52:40,680 --> 00:52:42,398
It's all my fault.
这都是我的错

758
00:52:45,080 --> 00:52:46,991
My father died in a cold world,
我的父亲死在了一个冰冷的世界
<i>（她父亲死在 Daleks 母星 Skaro）</i>

759
00:52:48,400 --> 00:52:50,596
a thousand light years away.
一千光年以外

760
00:52:51,360 --> 00:52:54,318
I died 15 years ago.
我15年前就死了

761
00:52:56,080 --> 00:52:57,434
Saw it in The Times.
我在《时代》杂志上看到了

762
00:52:58,320 --> 00:53:00,755
"Professor Edward Travers,”
“爱德华-特拉弗斯教授”

763
00:53:01,320 --> 00:53:02,640
CBE.
大英帝国勋章(fixme)

764
00:53:03,440 --> 00:53:05,113
Silly old fool.
老糊涂

765
00:53:06,800 --> 00:53:07,756
(CHUCKLING)

766
00:53:08,600 --> 00:53:10,716
"No flowers, by request.”
“应家属请求, 不要送花”

767
00:53:12,560 --> 00:53:14,392
But they still sent them.
但他们还是送来了花

768
00:53:15,800 --> 00:53:17,199
No one listens.
都不听

769
00:53:18,400 --> 00:53:20,914
Sometimes I can't remember his face.
有时我记不起他的面容

770
00:53:24,760 --> 00:53:26,592
And I've travelled in time.
但我穿越了时间

771
00:53:28,480 --> 00:53:30,278
Where do I belong now?
我现在属于什么地方？

772
00:53:33,720 --> 00:53:34,994
Don't you see?
你不明白吗？

773
00:53:36,440 --> 00:53:37,760
We've been tricked.
我们被耍了

774
00:53:38,920 --> 00:53:42,197
It was the Intelligence all the time!
一直都是大智慧

775
00:53:44,760 --> 00:53:46,592
Unfinished business.
它未尽的事业(fixme)

776
00:53:46,720 --> 00:53:48,518
(BOOMING)

777
00:53:49,240 --> 00:53:51,277
(LIGHTNING CRASHING)

778
00:54:09,000 --> 00:54:12,000
<i>(Terminal Accessed)</i>
<i>（电脑文字：终端访问已接入）</i>

779
00:54:15,280 --> 00:54:18,113
What now, sir?
Take the place by storm?
现在怎样，长官？fixme

780
00:54:18,240 --> 00:54:19,594
If we must.
如果必须的话

781
00:54:22,280 --> 00:54:24,590
Damnation. I'm an old fool.
见鬼，我真是老糊涂了

782
00:54:24,720 --> 00:54:25,755
- Sir?  - My gun.
- 怎么  - 我的枪

783
00:54:25,880 --> 00:54:27,109
I didn't pick it up.
我没拿起来

784
00:54:27,240 --> 00:54:30,312
- Want to go back?
- Too late for that, now. Come on.
- 想回去吗？  - 来不及了。现在走吧

785
00:54:32,240 --> 00:54:34,151
(DISTORTED) Intruders.
有人入侵

786
00:54:35,280 --> 00:54:39,035
Go. Greet them.
去，问候一下他们

787
00:54:39,160 --> 00:54:41,231
(ENERGY PULSATING)

788
00:54:49,520 --> 00:54:53,832
Sir, something rotten
in here, sir. I can feel it.
长官，这里有什么东西坏掉了，我能感觉到

789
00:54:53,960 --> 00:54:56,076
Too quiet. Come on.
太安静。快来

790
00:54:57,960 --> 00:54:59,359
Let's start at the top.
我们先从上面开始

791
00:55:07,520 --> 00:55:08,954
Sorry, sir.
抱歉，长官

792
00:55:09,080 --> 00:55:12,391
1 give up, Hinton.
Am I asleep or are you dead?
我放弃了，辛顿。是我在睡觉还是你死了？

793
00:55:12,520 --> 00:55:13,874
I never did philosophy, sir.
我不玩哲学，长官

794
00:55:14,000 --> 00:55:16,071
You're in the lift.
I'm in the computer systems.
你在电梯里，我在电脑系统里

795
00:55:16,200 --> 00:55:17,634
We have interface.
我们就有了交互界面

796
00:55:17,760 --> 00:55:20,479
So I'm talking to a ghost in a machine.
这么说我是在跟机器里面的一个鬼魂说话

797
00:55:21,280 --> 00:55:22,918
And what's the warning this time?
这次又是什么警告？

798
00:55:23,040 --> 00:55:26,158
The Intelligence has got into the
logic systems of New World's computers.
大智慧已经进入新世界的电脑系统了

799
00:55:26,280 --> 00:55:27,839
I snuck a ride too.
我也偷偷搭便车

800
00:55:27,960 --> 00:55:31,157
It's a virus. It's already spreading
across the Internet.
是一种病毒，已经散布到整个因特网了

801
00:55:31,280 --> 00:55:33,237
Transmitted from this building.
是从这栋建筑传送出去的

802
00:55:33,360 --> 00:55:36,671
I'll take you in as far as
I can, sir. Trust me.
我尽力带你进去，相信我

803
00:55:37,160 --> 00:55:38,480
You've said that before.
你以前也说过这话

804
00:55:38,600 --> 00:55:39,749
Sir?
长官？

805
00:55:41,880 --> 00:55:44,759
Nothing, Sergeant.
I just walked over someone's grave.
没什么，上士。我刚碰到鬼了

806
00:55:46,120 --> 00:55:48,316
Come on, Hinton! Come on!
快啊，辛顿！快点

807
00:55:57,840 --> 00:55:59,433
- I thought that you were dead.
- Maybe.
- 我以为你已经死了  - 也许

808
00:56:00,200 --> 00:56:02,237
I need your help, Kate.
So does your dad.
我需要你的帮助，凯特，你爸爸也需要

809
00:56:02,360 --> 00:56:03,316
Right.
好

810
00:56:07,000 --> 00:56:09,958
It's no good, sir. Something's jamming it.
这没用的，被什么东西卡住了

811
00:56:12,000 --> 00:56:13,229
I'm not used to this system.
我不熟悉这个系统

812
00:56:13,360 --> 00:56:14,430
But I am.
但我熟

813
00:56:14,560 --> 00:56:17,393
Ever heard of automatic writing?
Fingers on the keys.
听说过知道写文章吗？把手指放上去

814
00:56:33,960 --> 00:56:36,634
(HOUSE MUSIC PLAYING
THROUGH HEADPHONES)

815
00:56:44,760 --> 00:56:46,717
HINTON: Something's moving that lift.
有什么东西在控制那个电梯

816
00:56:47,480 --> 00:56:50,472
Option. A-D-stroke-Alt-three. Hit four.
Option键，A-D，敲Alt-3，按4

817
00:56:55,240 --> 00:56:56,799
It's like a morgue, sir.
像个停尸房，长官

818
00:56:58,320 --> 00:56:59,276
Like a trap.
像是个陷阱

819
00:56:59,960 --> 00:57:01,155
Back the other way.
回去那边

820
00:57:14,600 --> 00:57:15,590
HINTON: Stop that lift!
停掉那个电梯

821
00:57:15,720 --> 00:57:17,791
Option, three-stroke-Alt-four.
Option键，Alt-4敲三遍

822
00:57:20,240 --> 00:57:21,958
Brigadier, Get back!
准将，回去！

823
00:57:22,720 --> 00:57:23,835
You...
你...

824
00:57:24,680 --> 00:57:27,035
Get out of my head.
滚出我的脑袋

825
00:57:27,160 --> 00:57:28,798
I've had enough of your tricks.
我已经受够了你的伎俩

826
00:57:29,320 --> 00:57:31,834
I was wrong. Please!
我之前错了，求你了！

827
00:57:31,960 --> 00:57:34,110
Get away from the lift!
离开那个电梯！

828
00:57:34,240 --> 00:57:35,639
It's fighting back.
它在反击了

829
00:57:35,760 --> 00:57:37,353
Alt-four again. Hold it down!
再按 Alt-4。按住了

830
00:57:37,960 --> 00:57:41,635
Come away, please, Brigadier.
You shouldn't have come here.
你走吧, 准将。你不该来这里的

831
00:57:41,760 --> 00:57:43,717
It's a bit late for apologies, Madam.
现在道歉晚了点吧，女士

832
00:57:45,400 --> 00:57:46,356
Hold it there!
按住了！

833
00:57:46,480 --> 00:57:47,959
I can't keep it down.
我按不住了

834
00:57:48,800 --> 00:57:50,552
Go back to your studies.
回去继续学习

835
00:57:50,680 --> 00:57:52,000
There's nothing here you want!
这里没有你们想要的东西

836
00:57:52,120 --> 00:57:53,076
(THUDDING)

837
00:57:53,680 --> 00:57:54,670
Quickly.
快

838
00:58:00,280 --> 00:58:01,475
This way.
这边

839
00:58:02,160 --> 00:58:03,719
HARRODS: Look out, sir!
小心，长官！

840
00:58:04,640 --> 00:58:06,358
Leave him alone!
放开他！

841
00:58:11,960 --> 00:58:13,359
Hold it down!
按住！

842
00:58:13,480 --> 00:58:14,436
(BANG)

843
00:58:16,240 --> 00:58:18,390
(ROARING)

844
00:58:20,000 --> 00:58:23,197
TRAVERS: Acolytes! You know me!
助手们，你们认识我的！

845
00:58:24,320 --> 00:58:26,072
Stand away!
都闪开！

846
00:58:26,200 --> 00:58:27,270
Travers?

847
00:58:31,120 --> 00:58:33,589
Release him! Let him go free!
放开他！让他走！

848
00:58:36,400 --> 00:58:38,471
(ROARING)

849
00:58:44,160 --> 00:58:46,197
(SCREAMING)

850
00:58:49,320 --> 00:58:50,958
Must shut down the database.
必须关闭数据库了

851
00:58:51,800 --> 00:58:53,438
VICTORIA: Leave him alone!
放开他！

852
00:58:54,920 --> 00:58:56,718
(ROARING)

853
00:58:57,720 --> 00:59:00,951
All right. I was coming anyway.
好吧。反正我也会来的

854
00:59:02,040 --> 00:59:04,839
DISTORTED VOICE: What happened
to your faith, old man?
你的信念怎么了，老头？

855
00:59:05,720 --> 00:59:08,712
Huh? I saw your
Light of Truth, that's what!
